channel.description:
ok, nice and quick, how do i sort out these bloody nulls? if im in the wrong section or you think the client section would give better responses then tell me please. also rep++ if you can help me succesfully.

item.dc:creator: @II_Jacob_II II Jacob II
item.description:
@II_Jacob_II wrote:

[quote=“kickingjamie, post:4, topic:392220”][quote author=II Jacob II link=topic=489387.msg3577947#msg3577947 date=1303579320]
Yes, wrong section mate, it’s client sided, it’s to do with your cache/client it’s either your cache doesn’t contain the models for the certain items, or the client hasnt had them coded in so it isnt taking the model and using it for the items that why I personaly don’t use delta anymore although it isnt bad, anyway for a better explanation, or a client with a cache that suits the source, head over to the ‘Client Help’ section.

http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/board,138.0.html
[/quote]
you have insulted me :’( this server and client is not delta, anyways thanks for your help. one last question how long do you think it would take to fix all these nulls? i want to work on a v2 of my server but i cant without a decent client.[/quote]

Oh, what base is it then, because It isnt PI or Hyperion, I know that for sure.

item.title: Client or server problems, dont know which.. (nulls)
item.dc:creator: @doom_j doom_j
item.description:
@doom_j wrote:

Well it can be both client and server side, you get null items when the client you use doesn’t have the correct id for that item like dragon full helm, it isn’t in some client so when you use a client with out the model you get the item null on that client and the dragon full helm model on the one supporting it. I suggest you find a client that supports the items you have in your bank.
